  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C).",
    "Rinse the cod fillets and pat them dry with paper towels.",
    "In a small bowl, mix together the creamy sauce mix and lemon juice.",
    "Place the cod fillets in a baking dish and pour the creamy sauce mixture over them.",
    "Sprinkle the crisp breadcrumbs over the top of the cod.",
    "Dot the top of the cod with butter.",
    "Season with salt and black pepper to taste.",
    "Bake for 12-15 minutes, or until the cod is cooked through and the topping is golden brown.",
    "Garnish with chopped parsley and serve hot."
